message.body: people forget that zeronet is not an anonimity network, it's simply a decentralized network, and it's therefor not usefullas a replacement for tor
i2p, while it is designed withanonimity in mind, it has no link with the clearnet like tor has, tor is usable for accessing regular websites (kindof) i2p is not
also if anyone has a good starting point for getting around in i2p let me know, i've never been able to get any use out of it, most sites simply didn't work and others were way to basic
